dc_title_s: Plymouth County, Iowa, 1949, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet labels. Images are photoreductions of mosaics created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BKN. Form of individual image numbering: BKN-1F-[number], BKN-2F-[number], BKN-3F-[number], BKN-4F-[number], or BKN-5F-[number]."Flying completed 8-23-49." Flown by Woltz Studios, Des Moines, Iowa."Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
